The problem is the Broodmother kills the other Giant then will come after him, if he is still alive she may kill him , or you.<br>
Grab a group.<br>
<br>
At 40 you can solo the snow griffs, I did it at 35. They are however dangerous and scary.<br>
Acid is turned in in Thurg then you go to the hunter the other side of the wurm cave to get the control harness, then stage a group North of the Giant Fort on the ledge not far away. When they are ready, you get invis, enter wurm cave , give the control harness to the Broodmom.<br>
She will go to the giant fort and attack a giant named Gilak, Fergul will run, wait until he runs.<br>
When he does the group on the ledge should get him, he will run right into them.<br>
Kill him fast.<br>
He will have the leggings for loot.<br>
He will not have the leggings before then, killing him before hand gains you nothing. He respawn and respawn when you give the harness and has the leggings then.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
